               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-1279" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1279" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1279" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1279" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer, and live in Star-street, Paddington. No the morning of the 5th of April I was at work at Hyde-park-corner, open ing a drain—I hung my jacket on the rails by the triumphal arch, near where I was working—I had a tobacco-box, a knife, a chisel, and two keys, in the pocket—I saw the prisoner standing by, just before a coal-wagon came by—I looked round the hind part of the coal-wagon, and saw him running away with my jacket—I ran after him, calling "Stop thief," and he dropped it—I took him, and my fellow-workman picked up the jacket, and gave it to the policeman—this now produced is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You say you saw him with the jacket? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, under his left arm.</p>
